[[Category:Pages to sort]] [[Category:qq]][[de:May 21 (Lunisolar)]][[Category:qq]] [[Category:qq]]{{DEFAULTSORT:May 21 (Lunisolar)}}[[Category:qq]] [[cdo:5 nguŏk 21 hô̤ (nùng-lĭk)]] [[Category:Pages to sort]] [[Category:qq]][[de:May 21 (Lunisolar)]][[Category:qq]] [[Category:qq]]{{DEFAULTSORT:May 21 (Lunisolar)}}[[Category:qq]] [[zh-min-nan:5 goe̍h 21 ji̍t (kū-le̍k)]] [[Category:Pages to sort]] [[Category:qq]][[de:May 21 (Lunisolar)]][[Category:qq]] [[Category:qq]]{{DEFAULTSORT:May 21 (Lunisolar)}}[[Category:qq]] [[zh-yue:五月廿一]] {{Lunisolar May}} '''May 21''' is the 21st day of month {{ill|May (Lunisolar)|ja|5月 (旧暦)|lt=May|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} the 5th month of the traditional {{ill|Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|ja|旧暦|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|11=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} . It's {{ill|Rokuyō|ja|六曜|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} day is {{ill|Senshō|ja|先勝|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} . == Events == * Year 4 of {{ill|Yōrō|ja|養老|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} (Julian calendar {{ill|July 1|ja|7月1日|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} , [[720]] ) – {{ill|Prince Toneri|ja|舎人親王|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} and others present the {{ill|Nihon Shoki|ja|日本書紀|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} , consisting of 30 volumes and one volume of genealogies. * Year 4 of {{ill|Kōan (Japan)|ja|弘安|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} (Julian calendar {{ill|June 9|ja|6月9日|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} , [[1281]] ) – {{ill|Mongol invasions of Japan|ja|元寇|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} , {{ill|Goryeo|ja|高麗|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} warships attack {{ill|Iki Island|ja|壱岐|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} and {{ill|Tsushima Island|ja|対馬|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} , marking the beginning of the {{ill|Kōan campaign|ja|弘安の役|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} . * Year 3 of {{ill|Tenshō|ja|天正|1=Tenshō (Momoyama period)|lt=Tenshō Era|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} (Julian calendar {{ill|June 29|ja|6月29日|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} , [[1575]] ) – The {{ill|Battle of Nagashino|ja|長篠の戦い|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} takes place. * Year 10 of {{ill|Bunsei|ja|文政|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} (Gregorian calendar {{ill|June 15|ja|6月15日|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} , [[1827]] ) – {{ill|Rai San'yō|ja|頼山陽|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} presents his {{ill|Nihon Gaishi|ja|日本外史|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} , a 22-volume history of Japan, to senior councillor {{ill|Matsudaira Sadanobu|ja|松平定信|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} . * Year 2 of {{ill|Meiji|ja|明治|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} (Gregorian calendar {{ill|June 30|ja|6月30日|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} , [[1869]] ) – Japan's first {{ill|Elementary school|ja|小学校|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} opens in {{ill|Kyoto|ja|京都市|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} .
