{{Lunisolar May}} '''May 21''' is the 21st day of month {{ill|May (Lunisolar)|ja|5月 (旧暦)|lt=May (Satsuki)}} the 5th month of the traditional {{ill|Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|ja|旧暦|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|11=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar}} . It's {{ill|Rokuyō|ja|六曜}} day is {{ill|Senshō|ja|先勝}} . == Events == * Year 4 of {{ill|Yōrō|ja|養老}} (Julian calendar {{ill|July 1|ja|7月1日}} , [[720]] ) – {{ill|Prince Toneri|ja|舎人親王}} and others present the {{ill|Nihon Shoki|ja|日本書紀}} , consisting of 30 volumes and one volume of genealogies. * Year 4 of {{ill|Kōan (Japan)|ja|弘安}} (Julian calendar {{ill|June 9|ja|6月9日}} , [[1281]] ) – {{ill|Mongol invasions of Japan|ja|元寇}} , {{ill|Goryeo|ja|高麗}} warships attack {{ill|Iki Island|ja|壱岐}} and {{ill|Tsushima Island|ja|対馬}} , marking the beginning of the {{ill|Kōan campaign|ja|弘安の役}} . * Year 3 of {{ill|Tenshō|ja|天正|1=Tenshō (Momoyama period)|lt=Tenshō Era}} (Julian calendar {{ill|June 29|ja|6月29日}} , [[1575]] ) – The {{ill|Battle of Nagashino|ja|長篠の戦い}} takes place. * Year 10 of {{ill|Bunsei|ja|文政}} (Gregorian calendar {{ill|June 15|ja|6月15日}} , [[1827]] ) – {{ill|Rai San'yō|ja|頼山陽}} presents his {{ill|Nihon Gaishi|ja|日本外史}} , a 22-volume history of Japan, to senior councillor {{ill|Matsudaira Sadanobu|ja|松平定信}} . * Year 2 of {{ill|Meiji|ja|明治|1=Meiji era}} (Gregorian calendar {{ill|June 30|ja|6月30日}} , [[1869]] ) – Japan's first {{ill|Elementary school|ja|小学校}} opens in {{ill|Kyoto|ja|京都市}} .
