'''May 21''' is the 21st day of month {{ill|May (Lunisolar)|ja|5月 (旧暦)|lt=May (Satsuki)|qq=|12=draft}}  the 5th month of the traditional {{ill|Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|ja|旧暦|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|11=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|qq=|12=draft}} . It's {{ill|Rokuyō|ja|六曜|qq=|12=draft}}  day is {{ill|Senshō|ja|先勝|qq=|12=draft}} . 
== Events ==
* Year 4 of {{ill|Yōrō|ja|養老|qq=|12=draft}}  (Julian calendar {{ill|July 1|ja|7月1日|qq=|12=draft}} , [[720]] ) – {{ill|Prince Toneri|ja|舎人親王|qq=|12=draft}}  and others present the {{ill|Nihon Shoki|ja|日本書紀|qq=|12=draft}} , consisting of 30 volumes and one volume of genealogies.
* Year 4 of {{ill|Kōan (Japan)|ja|弘安|qq=|12=draft}}  (Julian calendar {{ill|June 9|ja|6月9日|qq=|12=draft}} , [[1281]] ) – {{ill|Mongol invasions of Japan|ja|元寇|qq=|12=draft}} , {{ill|Goryeo|ja|高麗|qq=|12=draft}}  warships attack {{ill|Iki Island|ja|壱岐|qq=|12=draft}}  and {{ill|Tsushima Island|ja|対馬|qq=|12=draft}} , marking the beginning of the {{ill|Kōan campaign|ja|弘安の役|qq=|12=draft}} .
* Year 3 of {{ill|Tenshō|ja|天正|1=Tenshō (Momoyama period)|lt=Tenshō Era|qq=|12=draft}}  (Julian calendar {{ill|June 29|ja|6月29日|qq=|12=draft}} , [[1575]] ) – The {{ill|Battle of Nagashino|ja|長篠の戦い|qq=|12=draft}}  takes place.
* Year 10 of {{ill|Bunsei|ja|文政|qq=|12=draft}}  (Gregorian calendar {{ill|June 15|ja|6月15日|qq=|12=draft}} , [[1827]] ) – {{ill|Rai San'yō|ja|頼山陽|qq=|12=draft}}  presents his {{ill|Nihon Gaishi|ja|日本外史|qq=|12=draft}} , a 22-volume history of Japan, to senior councillor {{ill|Matsudaira Sadanobu|ja|松平定信|qq=|12=draft}} .
* Year 2 of {{ill|Meiji|ja|明治|1=Meiji era|qq=|12=draft}}  (Gregorian calendar {{ill|June 30|ja|6月30日|qq=|12=draft}} , [[1869]] ) – Japan's first {{ill|Elementary school|ja|小学校|qq=|12=draft}}  opens in {{ill|Kyoto|ja|京都市|qq=|12=draft}} .

