{{Not to be confused with|May 21|qq=May 21}}[[Category:Days of the Japanese Lunisolar Calendar]]<!--why is this category always showing up as 347 members?--> {{afc comment|1=This article as with the other date articles is relatively limited in scope to Japan. Reviewing the translation of this is good and also adding content translated from Chinese and Korean wikipedias will also be good. Both wikipedias are also relatively centered around their own countries for their Lunisolar calendar dates[[User:Immanuelle|Immanuelle]] ([[User talk:Immanuelle|talk]]) 00:16, 28 April 2025 (UTC)}} {{Globalize|article|Japan|date=April 2025}} {{Expand Chinese|1=五月廿一|topic=hist|date=April 2025}} {{Expand Korean|1=음력 5월 21일|topic=hist|date=April 2025}} {{Lunisolar May|qq=}} '''May 21''' is the 21st day of month {{ill|May (Lunisolar)|ja|5月 (旧暦)|lt=May (Satsuki)|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/May (Lunisolar)|qq=}} the 5th month of the traditional {{ill|Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|ja|旧暦|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|11=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|13=User:Immanuelle/Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|qq=}} . It's {{ill|Rokuyō|ja|六曜|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Rokuyō|qq=}} day is {{ill|Senshō|ja|先勝|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Senshō|qq=}} . == Events == * Year 4 of [[:en:Yōrō|Yōrō]] (Julian calendar [[:en:July 1|July 1]] , [[720]] ) – [[:en:Prince Toneri|Prince Toneri]] and others present the [[:en:Nihon Shoki|Nihon Shoki]] , consisting of 30 volumes and one volume of genealogies. * Year 4 of [[:en:Kōan (Kamakura period)|Kōan (Japan)]] (Julian calendar [[:en:June 9|June 9]] , [[1281]] ) – [[:en:Mongol invasions of Japan|Mongol invasions of Japan]] , [[:en:Goryeo|Goryeo]] warships attack {{ill|Iki Island|ja|壱岐|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Iki Island|qq=}} and [[:en:Tsushima Island|Tsushima Island]] , marking the beginning of the [[:en:Battle of Kōan|Kōan campaign]] . * Year 3 of [[:en:Tenshō (Momoyama period)|Tenshō Era]] (Julian calendar [[:en:June 29|June 29]] , [[1575]] ) – The [[:en:Battle of Nagashino|Battle of Nagashino]] takes place. * Year 10 of [[:en:Bunsei|Bunsei]] (Gregorian calendar [[:en:June 15|June 15]] , [[1827]] ) – [[:en:Rai San'yō|Rai San'yō]] presents his [[:en:Nihon Gaishi|Nihon Gaishi]] , a 22-volume history of Japan, to senior councillor [[:en:Matsudaira Sadanobu|Matsudaira Sadanobu]] . * Year 2 of [[:en:Meiji era|Meiji era]] (Gregorian calendar [[:en:June 30|June 30]] , [[1869]] ) – Japan's first [[:en:Primary school|Elementary school]] opens in [[:en:Kyoto|Kyoto]] .
