:Kōan (Kamakura period)|Kōan (Japan)]] (Julian calendar [[:en:June 9|June 9]] , [[:en:1281|1281]] ) – [[:en:Mongol invasions of Japan|Mongol invasions of Japan]] , [[:en:Goryeo|Goryeo]] warships attack {{ill|Iki Island|ja|壱岐|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Iki Island|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 壱岐島}} and [[:en:Tsushima Island|Tsushima Island]] , marking the beginning of the [[:en:Battle of Kōan|Kōan campaign]] . * Year 3 of [[:en:Tenshō (Momoyama period)|Tenshō Era]] (Julian calendar [[:en:June 29|June 29]] , [[:en:1575|1575]] ) – The [[:en:Battle of Nagashino|Battle of Nagashino]] takes place. * Year 10 of [[:en:Bunsei|Bunsei]] (Gregorian calendar [[:en:June 15|June 15]] , [[:en:1827|1827]] ) – [[:en:Rai San'yō|Rai San'yō]] presents his [[:en:Nihon Gaishi|Nihon Gaishi]] , a 22-volume history of Japan, to senior councillor [[:en:Matsudaira Sadanobu|Matsudaira Sadanobu]] . * Year 2 of [[:en:Meiji era|Meiji era]] (Gregorian calendar [[:en:June 30|June 30]] , [[:en:1869|1869]] ) – Japan's first [[:en:Primary school|Elementary school]] opens in [[:en:Kyoto|Kyoto]] .
