* Year 4 of {{ill|Kōan (Kamakura period)|en|Kōan (Kamakura period)|qid=Q389180|lt=Kōan (Japan)|1=Kōan (Kamakura period)}}  (Julian calendar {{ill|June 9|en|June 9|qid=Q2618|lt=June 9|1=June 9}} , {{ill|1281|en|1281|qid=Q5537|lt=1281|1=1281}} ) – {{ill|Mongol invasions of Japan|en|Mongol invasions of Japan|qid=Q208156|lt=Mongol invasions of Japan|1=Mongol invasions of Japan}} , {{ill|Goryeo|en|Goryeo|qid=Q28208|lt=Goryeo|1=Goryeo}}  warships attack {{ill|Iki Island|ja|壱岐|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Iki Island|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 壱岐島}}  and {{ill|Tsushima Island|en|Tsushima Island|qid=Q52051|lt=Tsushima Island|1=Tsushima Island}} , marking the beginning of the {{ill|Battle of Kōan|en|Battle of Kōan|qid=Q2237622|lt=Kōan campaign|1=Battle of Kōan}} .
* Year 3 of {{ill|Tenshō (Momoyama period)|en|Tenshō (Momoyama period)|qid=Q1145058|lt=Tenshō Era|1=Tenshō (Momoyama period)}}  (Julian calendar {{ill|June 29|en|June 29|qid=Q2659|lt=June 29|1=June 29}} , {{ill|1575|en|1575|qid=Q6688|lt=1575|1=1575}} ) – The {{ill|Battle of Nagashino|en|Battle of Nagashino|qid=Q428369|lt=Battle of Nagashino|1=Battle of Nagashino}}  takes place.
* Year 10 of {{ill|Bunsei|en|Bunsei|qid=Q1327119|lt=Bunsei|1=Bunsei}}  (Gregorian calendar {{ill|June 15|en|June 15|qid=Q2613|lt=June 15|1=June 15}} , {{ill|1827|en|1827|qid=Q7008|lt=1827|1=1827}} ) – {{ill|Rai San'yō|en|Rai San'yō|qid=Q153320|lt=Rai San'yō|1=Rai San'yō}}  presents his {{ill|Nihon Gaishi|en|Nihon Gaishi|qid=Q835469|lt=Nihon Gaishi|1=Nihon Gaishi}} , a 22-volume history of Japan, to senior councillor {{ill|Matsudaira Sadanobu|en|Matsudaira Sadanobu|qid=Q284038|lt=Matsudaira Sadanobu|1=Matsudaira Sadanobu}} .
* Year 2 of {{ill|Meiji era|en|Meiji era|qid=Q3125096|lt=Meiji era|1=Meiji era}}  (Gregorian calendar {{ill|June 30|en|June 30|qid=Q2657|lt=June 30|1=June 30}} , {{ill|1869|en|1869|qid=Q7720|lt=1869|1=1869}} ) – Japan's first {{ill|Primary school|en|Primary school|qid=Q9842|lt=Elementary school|1=Primary school}}  opens in {{ill|Kyoto|en|Kyoto|qid=Q34600|lt=Kyoto|1=Kyoto}} .

